4. quod: referring directly to nefas, and so a neuter accusative, which, but explaining ideo, and so a conjunction, because. But they are really the same thing ; cf. Gr. 240. a.

5. quid deinde, what follows? The answer is illud, etc. - hoc: more emphatic than haec, the usual form (3r. 195. d ), as dwelling more on the act independent of its name. — fuit: see Gr. 308. c. — malo: ab· lative of manner. For the thought, cf. pestiferum, 1. 58. 8.
